main event: Multicolored flashing lights observed in the sky moving erratically, possibly identified as Venus.
interesting points: The object was reported at Laredo AFB, Texas at 0420Z on 4 August 1965., The lights were described as moving in irregular motion and blinking red before disappearing., The husband and wife observed the object at different times and reported it., There was mention of a hissing sound thought to be heard by the observer., The object was estimated to have been visible for about 15 minutes.
witness description: A civilian couple, with the husband working at a railroad.
